<span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> heh, I found it a little amusing after I went back and actually read a little bit. Seems to me they spend a lot of the time arguing about the calendar, but at the same time at least they are arguing about a calendar and not about specific individuals;-P Oh well everyone has their focus. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uaakla2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>aakla2</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=ttp://www.geocities.com/aakla2/EQ000014.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 205<br> <font color=#993300>(3/22/01 5:37:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> A callendar system would be realy cool, but sadly I dont see it happening. a Callendar system is as forien to us (build guilds from Mith Marr) as a girl in a g-string bikini is in iran. a little history of mith marr ( in case anyone missed it before) and no im not saying that guilds from Tunare dont matter, and no im not trying to be arogant or anyting. im just restating what has been posted about this subject before.<br>
<br>
there was a guild called Clan Bloodclaws on Mith Marr, mostly beta players and they where the shit. they where basicly the best of the best. they where the first on our server to kill the big named mobs. when a server would go up Clan Bloodclaws (hearby to be refered to as CBC) would have Vox and nag dead in like 2 hours. now people would try to set up raids but there were not enough high level players to get a raid going fast enough,. and if a mixed raid was scheduled alot of poeple didnt show up. and since we hardly got a shot at vox or nag, when we did get a raid and beat CBC to it. we got our asses kicked. and CBC would come in and clean up the mess.<br>
<br>
&quot;If you want to kill vox or nag all you have to do is beat us to it&quot; it was that simple. there where no if, and's or buts about it. they where the toughest kid on the block and they made the rules. so eventualy Divine Destiny was born. this guild was made up of pretty much the rest of the hgih level players that where not in CBC. they went head to head with CBC and the momentum started to  change. <br>
<br>
during this time Thott and some other people decided to make 1 build guild that had all the hardcore Raiders in it. and they where going to form up and take on the toughest challenges the game had to offer. that was when Afterlife was formed. key members from Divine Destiny went over to AL. and the server was back in the same situation it was in before. now AL controled mobs on the server and if you wanted to kill one, &quot;All you have to do is beat us to it&quot; so this is the way it went. AL could form a spur of the moment raid and be anywhere they wanted to in under 30 miuntes.  VS and Trak would be dead within like an hour and a half after the server coming up, this was when only like 3 or 4 other servers had killed trak. <br>
<br>
The only way to get things done was to make big guilds, or make a small guild and have a good rep. then go and take what you wanted. if someone was there already, oh well you just wern't fast enough. this was bread into us from the beging, &quot;If you want it, you just have to beat us to it&quot; setting up a schedule for alot of us would be borring. you could take your time and dilly dally all you want. part of the challenge of the *uber mob/plane* is getting there first. <br>
<br>
but we do have a rotation set up for VS and Trak. that curently has i think 6 guild in it for VS, im not sure about trak. back on Mith marr (before the upgrade) Fear and Hate where just regular zones, and where empty like 75% of the time, if no one was up there you went up. if someone was then you looked for soemthing else to do. <br>
<br>
Dont take this post the wrong way, im not sayng that a callendar sucks etc etc.  im just saying that for alot of us its just to forein. having a callendar for us is the same as if someone thought that selibis was to crowded and it should have a callendar.<br>
<br>
well I realy should get back to work. take care.  <br>
